WEBVTT

00:01.070 --> 00:04.390
Please, don't try anything you're about to see at home.

00:04.760 --> 00:06.400
We're what you call experts.

00:08.280 --> 00:12.050
On this bigger-is-better episode of "Mythbusters",

00:14.020 --> 00:16.309
The team takes four fan favorites

00:16.370 --> 00:18.380
to infinity and beyond.

00:18.460 --> 00:19.460
"X" marks the spot.

00:19.640 --> 00:20.710
That's where we're aiming for.

00:20.710 --> 00:23.430
First, can Adam and Jamie whip up a weapon

00:23.550 --> 00:24.690
from a water heater?

00:25.120 --> 00:27.770
Favorite thing to blow up, right here!

00:28.640 --> 00:30.610
Then, will they make the earth move

00:30.610 --> 00:32.090
with earth movers?

00:32.090 --> 00:33.090
I'm Jamie Hyneman,

00:33.160 --> 00:36.140
and I'm gonna thread a needle with an excavator.

00:36.140 --> 00:36.940
Whoa! Stop!

00:37.090 --> 00:39.050
Meanwhile, Tory, Grant, and Kari

00:39.180 --> 00:40.950
turn into rocket scientists...

00:40.950 --> 00:43.000
I think we got a winning design here.

00:43.000 --> 00:46.240
to see if a flight by fireworks is really possible.

00:46.240 --> 00:48.770
Keep your hands inside the vehicle at all times.

00:48.770 --> 00:49.640
And finally,

00:49.760 --> 00:53.870
the team flings some bling in bird balance 2.0...

00:53.870 --> 00:55.160
All we need now are some supermodels.

00:55.160 --> 00:58.290
as they find out if a longer limo can give them

00:58.290 --> 01:00.380
the cliffhanger ending they need.

01:00.390 --> 01:01.850
Look at the back end!

01:01.860 --> 01:03.240
It's coming off the ground!

01:05.970 --> 01:07.840
Who are the mythbusters?

01:09.000 --> 01:10.140
Adam Savage...

01:10.260 --> 01:11.890
Eating food cooked with C4.

01:11.980 --> 01:13.200
And Jamie Hyneman.

01:15.140 --> 01:19.240
Between them, more than 30 years of special-effects experience.

01:19.700 --> 01:21.390
Together with Kari Byron,

01:21.550 --> 01:22.630
Right tool for the job.

01:22.730 --> 01:23.520
Tory Belleci...

01:23.710 --> 01:25.260
We only have one shot at this.

01:25.260 --> 01:26.640
and Grant Imahara.

01:26.980 --> 01:28.870
That was a great result!

01:29.110 --> 01:30.780
They don't just tell the myths.

01:32.200 --> 01:34.400
They put them to the test.

01:40.160 --> 01:42.270
Buckle up, because on "Mythbusters",

01:47.070 --> 01:47.880
What's that about?

01:48.070 --> 01:50.790
In this episode, we are working off suggestions

01:50.790 --> 01:52.260
from fans for stuff that we've already done

01:52.260 --> 01:53.850
that we didn't necessarily mess up,

01:54.290 --> 01:57.670
but they have a suggestion of a way we can bump it up a level,

01:57.750 --> 01:58.670
ramp it way up.

01:58.670 --> 01:59.280
Like what?

01:59.570 --> 02:00.550
Hot-water heaters.

02:00.720 --> 02:02.780
Fans love it when we blow them up,

02:02.910 --> 02:05.200
and they've noticed that they make fantastic rockets

02:05.200 --> 02:07.310
when you point them vertically.

02:07.640 --> 02:09.180
But now they want to know what happens

02:09.180 --> 02:11.350
if we point them horizontally.

02:11.490 --> 02:14.120
What kind of cannon would a hot-water heater make?

02:14.480 --> 02:15.100
I like that.

02:15.230 --> 02:17.250
All we have to do is take one out to the bomb range,

02:17.250 --> 02:19.120
strap it down, shoot it at something

02:19.200 --> 02:21.470
and see what kind of mayhem it causes.

02:21.520 --> 02:23.340
That's exactly what I was thinking.

02:23.880 --> 02:26.890
Ever since the first tank turned torpedo,

02:27.150 --> 02:29.830
water heaters have become a "Mythbusters" Favorite.

02:31.790 --> 02:34.300
And the new fan request is this --

02:35.410 --> 02:39.530
if you replace a vertical launch with a horizontal one,

02:40.350 --> 02:42.340
can you really create a cannon?

02:44.720 --> 02:47.750
To find out, the guys wash up at the bomb range

02:47.750 --> 02:49.810
armed with their weapon of choice.

02:50.290 --> 02:51.370
So, how do you want to set this thing up?

02:51.600 --> 02:52.780
Well, if the fans want to see

02:52.780 --> 02:54.440
a water heater made into a cannon,

02:54.440 --> 02:56.120
I guess we got to lie this thing on its side.

02:56.210 --> 02:57.810
And if we're going to shoot it on its side,

02:57.810 --> 03:00.960
I feel really strongly that we need to shoot it at something.

03:01.220 --> 03:03.600
Well, you want to go and find something to shoot at,

03:03.670 --> 03:04.800
and I'll set this up?

03:04.930 --> 03:05.900
I think it's a great plan.

03:07.340 --> 03:09.760
It's a divide-and-conquer-type plan

03:09.820 --> 03:11.770
that sees Jamie getting to grips

03:11.770 --> 03:13.820
with their pressure vessel in waiting.

03:14.330 --> 03:16.050
We've set off these water heaters before,

03:16.200 --> 03:17.700
and we've learned a couple of things.

03:17.700 --> 03:19.220
The first and most important

03:19.250 --> 03:22.270
is that you always want to be able to abort.

03:22.270 --> 03:24.590
I think we're losing pressure somewhere we can't see.

03:24.590 --> 03:25.530
We've just got to abort.

03:25.580 --> 03:27.110
All right. Well, I'll pull the valve.

03:28.700 --> 03:30.980
Sometimes things don't work the way you plan.

03:30.980 --> 03:32.370
So, in this case,

03:32.870 --> 03:35.150
we've got a valve that we can open like so,

03:35.160 --> 03:36.710
and that'll relieve the pressure.

03:37.040 --> 03:38.060
The other thing that we've done

03:38.430 --> 03:40.910
is that we've put a couple of pressure sensors here

03:41.000 --> 03:43.610
so we'll always know exactly what's in this tank,

03:43.610 --> 03:44.760
and we won't approach it

03:44.760 --> 03:46.950
unless these things are saying zero

03:47.300 --> 03:48.730
or unless we've opened the valve.

03:49.120 --> 03:50.320
So, that's the cannon...

03:50.950 --> 03:52.710
and here's the cannon fodder.

03:53.060 --> 03:55.440
Yep, Adam's become the man with a van.

03:56.140 --> 03:57.620
I know it's big and red,

03:57.620 --> 03:59.490
so it's kind of like hitting the broad side of the barn,

03:59.490 --> 04:01.560
but that's not gonna stop me from making a target,

04:01.560 --> 04:02.980
'cause targets are pretty.

04:03.560 --> 04:05.260
And with the target taking shape,

04:05.350 --> 04:07.130
that just leaves the lock and load,

04:07.440 --> 04:08.990
a process which starts

04:08.990 --> 04:11.050
with the addition of 30 gallons of water...

04:12.190 --> 04:15.210
My favorite things to blow up, right here!

04:15.500 --> 04:18.180
and ends with the unit being hammered into place.

04:19.310 --> 04:20.130
We're solid.

04:21.060 --> 04:23.270
With a mini bulldozer parked in place

04:23.270 --> 04:24.830
to further contain the cannon,

04:24.980 --> 04:26.350
the heater gets powered up.

04:27.180 --> 04:28.280
Shall I walk you through

04:28.280 --> 04:29.590
exactly what's gonna go down here?

04:31.200 --> 04:34.210
Actually, I think it's pretty clear what's gonna go down here!

04:34.670 --> 04:35.790
I think my work is done.

04:37.630 --> 04:38.860
But for any of you at home

04:38.880 --> 04:41.590
worried your water heater might also go ballistic,

04:42.100 --> 04:43.430
here's some reassurance.

04:44.470 --> 04:46.520
Why doesn't this happen in your house every day?

04:46.820 --> 04:48.600
Quite frankly, because they've designed it not to.

04:48.660 --> 04:49.680
And here's how.

04:50.010 --> 04:51.570
First, they don't restrict

04:51.740 --> 04:54.340
either the inlet or the outlet ports of the hot-water heater,

04:54.340 --> 04:56.630
so that's one place the overpressure can go.

04:56.950 --> 04:58.900
Secondly, there's a thermostat in here,

04:58.990 --> 05:01.630
which, when the hot-water heater's temperature gets too high,

05:02.030 --> 05:03.800
shuts off the power to both heating elements

05:03.970 --> 05:05.600
until the water heater cools down.

05:06.000 --> 05:07.310
Thirdly, and perhaps most importantly,

05:07.310 --> 05:09.750
is right here, when you install a hot-water heater,

05:09.750 --> 05:12.330
you must install an overpressure-relief valve.

05:12.440 --> 05:14.730
That means when the pressure in here gets too high,

05:15.040 --> 05:17.810
it goes -- and releases the water,

05:17.830 --> 05:20.080
thus releasing the pressure from the cannister.

05:20.770 --> 05:21.590
Needless to say,

05:21.660 --> 05:24.890
the mythbusters have disabled all of those features,

05:25.080 --> 05:27.450
which is why they've gone to hunker in the bunker.

05:27.980 --> 05:29.380
All we do now is wait.

05:29.380 --> 05:31.240
It's about halfway there, about 150 psi.

05:32.170 --> 05:33.130
I love this part.

05:33.660 --> 05:34.430
This kills me.

05:35.590 --> 05:38.330
From past experience, Adam and Jamie know that

05:38.330 --> 05:43.070
there's no blow until the pressure goes beyond 300 psi.

05:45.010 --> 05:46.500
And 40 minutes later...

05:46.810 --> 05:48.330
305 psi.

05:49.070 --> 05:50.570
They're right in that butter zone.

